Results C

## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test
## 
## data:  contingency_table_c
## X-squared = 5.5413, df = 2, p-value = 0.06262

Section (clear cut or old growth) does not have a significant effect on a salamander location within the channel (cascade, side-channel, pool) (\(\chi\)2(2)) = 5.5412722) (Table 1). For salamander observations in the clear cut section n = 368, for observations in the old growth section n = 320.

Results D

## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  pgs_og and pgs_cc
## t = -1.6669, df = 692.79, p-value = 0.09599
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -2.5972032  0.2121307
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##  6.583333  7.775870

Mean salamander weight in clear cut and old growth sections did not differ significantly in 2017 (t(692.79) = -1.67, p > 0.05). Mean salamander weight in the clear cut section was 18% greater than in the old growth section, with an actual difference of 1.19 grams. For salamanders observed in the clear cut section mean = 7.78g, n = 368, while for salamanders observed in the old growth section, mean = 6.58g, n = 320.
